fields.name: title

fields.value: Observational oceanographic data obtained from an Autonomous Underwater Vehicle survey.  Sensors record environmental parameters as the vehicle travels a programmed path through the water.  Those measurements have been processed by MBARI Matlab-based dorado science data processing toolbox into this data set.
fields.name: summary

fields.value: Follows CLIVAR (Climate Varibility and Predictability)  standards, cf. http://www.clivar.org/data/data_policy.php. Data available free of charge. User assumes all risk for use of data. User must display citation in any publication or product using data. User must contact PI prior to any commercial use of data.
fields.name: distribution_statement

fields.value: These data were collected and made freely available by the Monterey Bay Aquarium Research Institute.

fields.value: Hourly Gridded MBARI Mooring M1 Sea Water Temperature and Salinity Observations
fields.name: title

fields.value: These data have been processed from the original instrument netCDF files which have individual irregular time axes.  The data in this file have been combined on a common hourly time axes and a common nominal depth axis.  Data values outside of reasonable ranges have been flagged as bad.
fields.name: summary
